1
00:00:00,166 --> 00:00:02,366
很多人对纸最大的误解是
The biggest misconception about paper

2
00:00:02,600 --> 00:00:04,733
以为纸只是用来写字的
Is thinking it's just for writing

3
00:00:04,866 --> 00:00:05,666
不是
No

4
00:00:05,833 --> 00:00:08,000
纸真正改变命运的地方
Where paper really changed destiny

5
00:00:08,233 --> 00:00:10,300
是它让一个人的能力
Is it let one person's ability

6
00:00:10,333 --> 00:00:14,100
第一次可以被复制、被带走、被比较
Be copied, carried, and compared for the first time

7
00:00:14,333 --> 00:00:16,333
你以为读书改变命运
You think reading changes destiny

8
00:00:16,533 --> 00:00:17,900
但更早一步
But one step earlier

9
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:20,600
是纸改变了社会筛选人的方式
It was paper that changed how society selects people

10
00:00:20,766 --> 00:00:21,800
一张试卷
An exam paper

11
00:00:21,966 --> 00:00:23,000
一纸文书
An official document

12
00:00:23,166 --> 00:00:24,200
一份契约
A contract

13
00:00:24,433 --> 00:00:26,000
一张录取通知书
An admission letter

14
00:00:26,233 --> 00:00:28,233
这些东西看起来都很薄
These things look thin

15
00:00:28,533 --> 00:00:31,300
但它们经常决定一个人能不能被看见
But they often determine whether a person can be seen

16
00:00:31,400 --> 00:00:32,600
能不能被承认
Whether they can be recognized

17
00:00:32,766 --> 00:00:34,366
能不能进入下一扇门
Whether they can enter the next door

18
00:00:34,500 --> 00:00:36,566
这件事放到今天也一样
This still holds true today

19
00:00:36,733 --> 00:00:39,933
很多人以为 AI 时代最重要的是会不会提问
Many people think the most important thing in the AI era is knowing how to ask questions

20
00:00:40,133 --> 00:00:41,166
其实不是
Actually no

21
00:00:41,333 --> 00:00:43,033
真正拉开差距的
What truly sets people apart

22
00:00:43,400 --> 00:00:47,433
是你能不能把自己的判断、能力和作品
Is whether you can turn your judgment, skills, and work

23
00:00:47,700 --> 00:00:50,433
变成别人一眼能识别的信号
Into a signal others can spot at a glance

24
00:00:50,600 --> 00:00:53,200
古代那张纸，筛选读书人
That ancient paper filtered scholars

25
00:00:53,366 --> 00:00:57,433
今天的作品页、简历、账号、文档、视频
Today's portfolios, resumes, accounts, docs, and videos

26
00:00:57,633 --> 00:00:59,133
也在筛选普通人
Are filtering ordinary people too

27
00:00:59,200 --> 00:01:01,433
所以这条视频不讲纸的发明史
So this video isn't about the invention history of paper

28
00:01:01,566 --> 00:01:03,333
只讲一个反直觉的判断
It's about one counterintuitive insight

29
00:01:03,533 --> 00:01:07,100
纸改变命运，不是因为它承载了知识
Paper changed destiny not because it carried knowledge

30
00:01:07,233 --> 00:01:12,733
而是因为它把命运变成了一套可以被记录、比较和筛选的系统
But because it turned destiny into a system that could be recorded, compared, and filtered

31
00:01:12,800 --> 00:01:13,900
先想一个问题
Think about this first

32
00:01:14,200 --> 00:01:15,600
如果你很聪明
If you were smart

33
00:01:15,766 --> 00:01:18,033
但你生活在一个没有纸的时代
But you lived in an era without paper

34
00:01:18,200 --> 00:01:19,800
你怎么证明自己聪明？
How would you prove you were smart?

35
00:01:19,933 --> 00:01:20,833
你可以说
You could say

36
00:01:21,166 --> 00:01:22,133
我会背书
I can recite texts

37
00:01:22,333 --> 00:01:23,233
我会算账
I can do math

38
00:01:23,400 --> 00:01:24,566
我会写文章
I can write essays

39
00:01:24,766 --> 00:01:25,966
我有想法
I have ideas

40
00:01:26,166 --> 00:01:27,200
但问题是
But the problem is

41
00:01:27,533 --> 00:01:28,766
别人怎么知道？
How would anyone know?

42
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:30,633
你的想法留不下来
Your ideas couldn't be preserved

43
00:01:30,733 --> 00:01:32,233
你的文章传不远
Your writing couldn't travel far

44
00:01:32,366 --> 00:01:34,833
你的能力很难被一个陌生人验证
Your abilities were hard for a stranger to verify

45
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:37,833
这才是普通人真正被困住的地方
This is where ordinary people truly got stuck

46
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:39,433
不是你一定没有能力
It wasn't that they had no ability

47
00:01:39,633 --> 00:01:42,300
而是你的能力没有低成本的载体
It was that their ability had no low-cost medium

48
00:01:42,433 --> 00:01:43,633
竹简可以写
Bamboo slips could be written on

49
00:01:43,800 --> 00:01:45,033
木牍可以写
Wooden tablets could be written on

50
00:01:45,200 --> 00:01:46,300
丝帛也可以写
Silk could also be written on

51
00:01:46,433 --> 00:01:48,900
但它们不是太重，就是太贵
But they were either too heavy or too expensive

52
00:01:49,033 --> 00:01:51,166
一部书可能是一车竹简
One book might fill an entire cart of bamboo slips

53
00:01:51,333 --> 00:01:54,400
一段文字可能要靠人一笔一画抄下来
One passage might have to be copied stroke by stroke by hand

54
00:01:54,566 --> 00:01:55,700
这意味着什么？
What does that mean?

55
00:01:55,933 --> 00:01:57,700
意味着知识不是没有
It means knowledge wasn't absent

56
00:01:57,900 --> 00:01:59,133
但它很难流动
But it couldn't flow

57
00:01:59,333 --> 00:02:00,566
能力不是没有
Ability wasn't absent

58
00:02:00,733 --> 00:02:02,966
但它很难留下证据
But it couldn't leave evidence

59
00:02:03,133 --> 00:02:04,800
你今天觉得一张纸不值钱
You think a piece of paper is worthless today

60
00:02:05,133 --> 00:02:06,700
是因为它太容易得到
Because it's too easy to get

61
00:02:06,933 --> 00:02:09,000
可正因为它便宜，它才可怕
But precisely because it's cheap, it's powerful

62
00:02:09,233 --> 00:02:10,933
便宜，才会普及
Cheap means widespread

63
00:02:11,100 --> 00:02:13,033
普及，才会改变规则
Widespread means it changes the rules

64
00:02:13,200 --> 00:02:14,966
很多改变命运的东西
Many things that changed destiny

65
00:02:15,300 --> 00:02:17,900
一开始都不是看起来很高级的东西
Didn't look impressive at first

66
00:02:18,133 --> 00:02:20,133
它们只是把一件原来很贵的事
They just made something that used to be expensive

67
00:02:20,200 --> 00:02:21,500
变便宜了
 Cheap

68
00:02:21,700 --> 00:02:23,500
纸把记录变便宜
Paper made recording cheap

69
00:02:23,900 --> 00:02:25,100
把复制变便宜
Made copying cheap

70
00:02:25,400 --> 00:02:26,733
把携带变便宜
Made carrying cheap

71
00:02:27,033 --> 00:02:28,533
也把一个人的能力
Also made a person's abilities

72
00:02:28,600 --> 00:02:30,366
变得更容易被别人看到
Easier for others to see

73
00:02:30,600 --> 00:02:32,400
这就是纸的第一层反转
This is the first reversal about paper

74
00:02:32,566 --> 00:02:34,733
它不是把聪明人变聪明
It didn't make smart people smarter

75
00:02:34,833 --> 00:02:37,166
它是让聪明人更容易留下证据
It let smart people leave evidence more easily

76
00:02:37,300 --> 00:02:39,233
你有能力，但没人看见
You have ability but no one sees it

77
00:02:39,366 --> 00:02:42,733
和你没有能力，在结果上差别很小
And having no ability, in terms of results, aren't that different

78
00:02:42,900 --> 00:02:44,133
纸出现以后
After paper appeared

79
00:02:44,766 --> 00:02:47,700
很多人的想法第一次有机会离开自己的嘴巴
Many people's ideas could finally leave their own mouths

80
00:02:47,933 --> 00:02:49,400
离开自己的村子
Leave their own villages

81
00:02:49,566 --> 00:02:51,000
离开自己的身体
Leave their own bodies

82
00:02:51,166 --> 00:02:55,033
变成一张可以被传阅、保存、比较的东西
And become something that could be shared, saved, and compared

83
00:02:55,333 --> 00:02:56,600
这一步很重要
This step was crucial

84
00:02:56,766 --> 00:02:58,900
因为普通人想改变命运
Because for ordinary people to change their destiny

85
00:02:59,000 --> 00:03:01,400
第一件事不是证明自己很厉害
The first thing isn't proving you're amazing

86
00:03:01,600 --> 00:03:04,166
而是先让别人有机会看见你厉害
It's giving others a chance to see you're amazing

87
00:03:04,200 --> 00:03:06,800
但纸只让人被看见，还不够
But paper only let people be seen, that wasn't enough

88
00:03:06,966 --> 00:03:08,133
更关键的是
What mattered more was

89
00:03:08,300 --> 00:03:11,400
纸让社会开始用同一种方式比较人
Paper made society start comparing people the same way

90
00:03:11,566 --> 00:03:13,100
这听起来有点冷
This sounds cold

91
00:03:13,233 --> 00:03:14,366
但非常真实
But it's very real

92
00:03:14,533 --> 00:03:15,400
你看考试
Look at exams

93
00:03:15,566 --> 00:03:17,500
为什么一张试卷那么重要？
Why is one test paper so important?

94
00:03:17,633 --> 00:03:18,966
不是因为纸神圣
It's not because paper is sacred

95
00:03:19,100 --> 00:03:21,333
而是因为它把很多人的能力
But because it put many people's abilities

96
00:03:21,400 --> 00:03:23,000
放进了同一个格式里
Into the same format

97
00:03:23,166 --> 00:03:24,100
同一套题
The same questions

98
00:03:24,233 --> 00:03:25,333
同一段时间
The same time limit

99
00:03:25,500 --> 00:03:26,566
同一种评分
The same grading

100
00:03:26,733 --> 00:03:28,000
最后变成一个结果
Then it became a single result

101
00:03:28,166 --> 00:03:28,966
这时候
At that point

102
00:03:29,233 --> 00:03:32,633
人的命运就不再只靠熟人推荐
People's destiny no longer relied only on referrals from acquaintances

103
00:03:32,800 --> 00:03:34,233
不再只靠出身
No longer only on family background

104
00:03:34,366 --> 00:03:36,166
不再只靠谁认识谁
No longer only on who knew whom

105
00:03:36,333 --> 00:03:38,100
至少在某些场景里
At least in some scenarios

106
00:03:38,233 --> 00:03:41,000
它开始有了一套可以比较的标准
There was finally a standard for comparison

107
00:03:41,166 --> 00:03:43,133
这就是纸最狠的地方
This is paper's most powerful aspect

108
00:03:43,300 --> 00:03:45,133
它不只是传播知识
It didn't just spread knowledge

109
00:03:45,233 --> 00:03:46,766
它还制造标准
It created standards

110
00:03:46,966 --> 00:03:48,366
一张试卷是标准
An exam paper is a standard

111
00:03:48,500 --> 00:03:50,133
一份合同是标准
A contract is a standard

112
00:03:50,233 --> 00:03:51,633
一张户籍是标准
A household registration is a standard

113
00:03:51,800 --> 00:03:53,333
一纸任命是标准
An appointment letter is a standard

114
00:03:53,433 --> 00:03:55,766
一封录取通知书也是标准
An admission letter is also a standard

115
00:03:55,900 --> 00:03:58,733
中国人为什么对“纸”有一种很复杂的感情？
Why do Chinese people have such complex feelings about paper?

116
00:03:58,900 --> 00:04:00,500
因为我们太知道了
Because we know too well

117
00:04:00,766 --> 00:04:04,533
有些纸，拿到之前只是一张纸
Some papers, before you get them, they're just paper

118
00:04:04,733 --> 00:04:07,633
拿到之后，就是另一种人生
After you get them, they're a different life

119
00:04:07,766 --> 00:04:09,000
一张通知书
An admission letter

120
00:04:09,000 --> 00:04:11,566
可以让一个家庭突然安静几秒
Can make a family suddenly go quiet for a few seconds

121
00:04:11,700 --> 00:04:12,800
一张合同
A contract

122
00:04:12,900 --> 00:04:16,400
可以让一段合作从口头承诺变成责任
Can turn a verbal promise into a responsibility

123
00:04:16,566 --> 00:04:17,833
一张房产证
A property deed

124
00:04:18,033 --> 00:04:20,500
可以让一个人觉得自己终于落下来了
Can make someone feel they've finally found their footing

125
00:04:20,600 --> 00:04:21,800
一张判决书
A court verdict

126
00:04:21,900 --> 00:04:24,233
可以把一个人的后半生改写
Can rewrite the second half of someone's life

127
00:04:24,400 --> 00:04:25,400
纸很轻
Paper is light

128
00:04:25,633 --> 00:04:29,033
但社会把很多很重的东西写在了纸上
But society has written many heavy things on paper

129
00:04:29,233 --> 00:04:31,366
所以你不要把纸理解成工具
So don't think of paper as just a tool

130
00:04:31,533 --> 00:04:32,966
它更像一个接口
It's more like an interface

131
00:04:33,133 --> 00:04:35,033
个人通过它进入社会
Individuals enter society through it

132
00:04:35,333 --> 00:04:37,300
社会通过它识别个人
Society identifies individuals through it

133
00:04:37,500 --> 00:04:39,600
这就是为什么纸会改变命运
This is why paper changed destiny

134
00:04:39,733 --> 00:04:41,500
它让能力有了凭证
It gave ability a credential

135
00:04:41,700 --> 00:04:43,233
让规则有了形状
It gave rules a shape

136
00:04:43,400 --> 00:04:44,700
让机会有了入口
It gave opportunity an entrance

137
00:04:44,900 --> 00:04:47,533
也让比较变得更大规模
And it made comparison happen on a larger scale

138
00:04:47,700 --> 00:04:49,566
当然，这并不完美
Of course, this isn't perfect

139
00:04:49,766 --> 00:04:51,500
任何标准都会漏掉人
Any standard will miss people

140
00:04:51,600 --> 00:04:53,400
任何考试都会筛错人
Any exam will filter out the wrong people

141
00:04:53,566 --> 00:04:57,533
任何纸面资格，都可能遮住真实能力
Any paper qualification can hide real ability

142
00:04:57,766 --> 00:04:58,933
但反过来说
But on the flip side

143
00:04:59,200 --> 00:05:00,733
没有这些纸
Without these papers

144
00:05:01,200 --> 00:05:04,200
普通人连被误判的机会都没有
Ordinary people wouldn't even have the chance to be misjudged

145
00:05:04,366 --> 00:05:05,833
他可能直接没有机会
They might just have no chance at all

146
00:05:05,966 --> 00:05:07,600
这就是最反直觉的地方
This is the most counterintuitive part

147
00:05:07,800 --> 00:05:10,200
纸带来的不是单纯的公平
Paper didn't bring simple fairness

148
00:05:10,366 --> 00:05:12,433
它带来的是一种新的竞争方式
It brought a new way of competing

149
00:05:12,700 --> 00:05:13,833
门打开了
The door opened

150
00:05:14,000 --> 00:05:15,133
人也变多了
And more people came in

151
00:05:15,300 --> 00:05:16,400
机会变大了
Opportunities grew

152
00:05:16,533 --> 00:05:17,766
压力也变大了
But so did the pressure

153
00:05:17,933 --> 00:05:19,600
纸让更多人能上桌
Paper let more people sit at the table

154
00:05:19,800 --> 00:05:22,500
但上桌之后，大家就要开始被比较
But once at the table, everyone starts getting compared

155
00:05:22,600 --> 00:05:24,600
讲到这里，你再看 AI
Now look at AI from this angle

156
00:05:24,966 --> 00:05:27,533
就会发现今天正在发生一件很像的事
And you'll see something very similar happening today

157
00:05:27,633 --> 00:05:31,133
很多人以为 AI 最大的影响是答案变多了
Many people think AI's biggest impact is more answers

158
00:05:31,200 --> 00:05:32,000
不是
No

159
00:05:32,200 --> 00:05:34,600
答案变多，只是表面
More answers is just the surface

160
00:05:34,800 --> 00:05:36,233
真正重要的是
What really matters is

161
00:05:36,500 --> 00:05:42,200
AI 正在让表达、整理、写作、做方案这些事
AI is making expression, organization, writing, and planning

162
00:05:42,200 --> 00:05:43,300
变得非常便宜
Incredibly cheap

163
00:05:43,566 --> 00:05:45,100
过去你写一篇稿子
In the past, writing one draft

164
00:05:45,233 --> 00:05:46,700
可能要憋一下午
Might take you all afternoon

165
00:05:46,833 --> 00:05:49,300
现在 AI 可以先给你十个版本
Now AI can give you ten versions first

166
00:05:49,400 --> 00:05:51,133
过去你整理一份资料
In the past, organizing research

167
00:05:51,300 --> 00:05:53,033
可能要翻很多页面
Might mean flipping through many pages

168
00:05:53,233 --> 00:05:55,733
现在 AI 可以先给你一个框架
Now AI can give you a framework first

169
00:05:55,933 --> 00:05:57,400
过去一个人不会写
In the past, if someone couldn't write

170
00:05:57,500 --> 00:05:59,200
就很难把想法讲清楚
They had a hard time explaining their ideas clearly

171
00:05:59,366 --> 00:06:00,900
现在不会写的人
Now people who can't write

172
00:06:00,966 --> 00:06:02,833
也能借工具写得像样
Can use tools to produce decent work

173
00:06:03,000 --> 00:06:04,366
这听起来很公平
This sounds fair

174
00:06:04,533 --> 00:06:06,033
但你仔细想一下
But think about it carefully

175
00:06:06,300 --> 00:06:08,933
当所有人都更容易表达以后
When everyone can express more easily

176
00:06:08,933 --> 00:06:11,333
表达本身就没那么稀缺了
Expression itself becomes less scarce

177
00:06:11,533 --> 00:06:13,966
当所有人都能生成内容以后
When everyone can generate content

178
00:06:14,100 --> 00:06:16,433
内容本身就没那么值钱了
Content itself becomes less valuable

179
00:06:16,633 --> 00:06:18,400
这和纸普及以后很像
This is a lot like after paper became widespread

180
00:06:18,700 --> 00:06:20,233
纸让更多人可以写
Paper let more people write

181
00:06:20,366 --> 00:06:22,166
但最后不是谁有纸谁赢
But in the end, it wasn't about who had paper

182
00:06:22,366 --> 00:06:23,600
而是谁写得准
It was about who wrote most precisely

183
00:06:23,800 --> 00:06:24,833
谁答得好
Who answered best

184
00:06:25,033 --> 00:06:26,600
谁能被标准识别
Who could be recognized by the standards

185
00:06:26,800 --> 00:06:27,966
AI 也是一样
Same with AI

186
00:06:28,233 --> 00:06:30,833
以后不是谁会打开 AI 谁赢
In the future, it won't be about who can open AI

187
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:32,966
而是谁能提出更好的问题
It'll be about who can ask better questions

188
00:06:33,333 --> 00:06:35,400
谁能判断答案有没有用
Who can judge whether an answer is useful

189
00:06:35,633 --> 00:06:37,733
谁能把 AI 生成的东西
Who can turn what AI generates

190
00:06:38,033 --> 00:06:39,600
变成自己的作品
Into their own original work

191
00:06:39,800 --> 00:06:41,633
普通人最该警惕的
What ordinary people should watch out for most

192
00:06:41,800 --> 00:06:43,900
不是 AI 抢走你的工作
Isn't AI taking your job

193
00:06:44,133 --> 00:06:46,366
而是你以为自己用了 AI
It's thinking that because you use AI

194
00:06:46,800 --> 00:06:48,700
就已经站在新世界里
You're already standing in the new world

195
00:06:48,800 --> 00:06:52,566
其实你可能只是更快地产出了一堆没有辨识度的东西
When really you might just be producing a pile of indistinguishable content faster

196
00:06:52,800 --> 00:06:54,233
这句话可能有点刺耳
This might sting a bit

197
00:06:54,400 --> 00:06:55,500
但很重要
But it's important

198
00:06:55,700 --> 00:06:57,766
AI 会让平庸变得更快
AI will make mediocrity faster

199
00:06:58,000 --> 00:07:01,533
也会让真正有判断的人，放大得更快
And it will amplify those with real judgment even faster

200
00:07:01,700 --> 00:07:03,700
工具不会自动给你命运
Tools won't automatically give you a destiny

201
00:07:03,833 --> 00:07:06,600
它只会放大你原来处理问题的方式
They only amplify how you originally solve problems

202
00:07:06,733 --> 00:07:07,766
你问题模糊
Your questions are vague

203
00:07:07,933 --> 00:07:09,566
它给你的答案也模糊
It gives you vague answers

204
00:07:09,700 --> 00:07:10,633
你没有标准
You have no standards

205
00:07:10,833 --> 00:07:12,200
它给你十个版本
It gives you ten versions

206
00:07:12,333 --> 00:07:13,733
你也不知道选哪一个
And you don't know which to pick

207
00:07:13,933 --> 00:07:15,500
你没有真实场景
You have no real scenarios

208
00:07:15,633 --> 00:07:18,033
它说得再顺，也落不到生活里
No matter how smooth it sounds, it won't land in your life

209
00:07:18,200 --> 00:07:20,300
所以 AI 时代的新纸是什么？
So what's the new paper in the AI era?

210
00:07:20,566 --> 00:07:22,000
不是一段提示词
It's not a prompt

211
00:07:22,233 --> 00:07:23,433
不是一堆回答
It's not a pile of answers

212
00:07:23,600 --> 00:07:25,100
而是你的作品
It's your work

213
00:07:25,300 --> 00:07:26,133
你的文章
Your writing

214
00:07:26,333 --> 00:07:27,133
你的视频
Your videos

215
00:07:27,566 --> 00:07:28,500
你的方案
Your proposals

216
00:07:28,700 --> 00:07:29,766
你的账号
Your accounts

217
00:07:30,000 --> 00:07:31,333
你的项目记录
Your project records

218
00:07:31,566 --> 00:07:34,366
这些东西会变成别人识别你的方式
These will become how others identify you

219
00:07:34,500 --> 00:07:37,733
就像过去一张试卷、一个文书、一份契约
Just like how an exam paper, a document, or a contract

220
00:07:37,766 --> 00:07:39,533
会让社会识别一个人
Used to let society identify a person

221
00:07:39,733 --> 00:07:43,300
今天，你留下的作品，也在替你说话
Today, the work you leave behind speaks for you

222
00:07:43,500 --> 00:07:46,333
你不在场的时候，它替你在场
When you're not there, it's there for you

223
00:07:46,533 --> 00:07:49,133
你不开口的时候，它替你开口
When you don't speak, it speaks for you

224
00:07:49,300 --> 00:07:51,000
你还没见到机会的时候
Before you even see the opportunity

225
00:07:51,233 --> 00:07:53,033
它先替你被别人看见
It gets seen by others first

226
00:07:53,100 --> 00:07:56,166
所以这条视频最后，只给一个建议
So just one piece of advice at the end of this video

227
00:07:56,333 --> 00:07:57,500
别只学习
Don't just learn

228
00:07:57,633 --> 00:07:58,900
别只收藏
Don't just collect

229
00:07:59,133 --> 00:08:00,233
别只问 AI
Don't just ask AI

230
00:08:00,533 --> 00:08:02,300
你要写出自己的那张纸
You need to write your own paper

231
00:08:02,433 --> 00:08:05,033
这里的“纸”，不一定是真的纸
This paper isn't necessarily a real piece of paper

232
00:08:05,200 --> 00:08:06,633
它可以是一篇文章
It could be an article

233
00:08:06,933 --> 00:08:08,133
可以是一条视频
It could be a video

234
00:08:08,500 --> 00:08:10,166
可以是一份作品集
It could be a portfolio

235
00:08:10,366 --> 00:08:12,366
可以是一份可复用的方案
It could be a reusable proposal

236
00:08:12,533 --> 00:08:14,533
可以是一个持续更新的账号
It could be a regularly updated account

237
00:08:14,700 --> 00:08:16,233
它的作用只有一个
It only serves one purpose

238
00:08:16,500 --> 00:08:18,200
让别人更容易看见你
To make it easier for others to see you

239
00:08:18,366 --> 00:08:19,633
更容易理解你
To understand you better

240
00:08:19,766 --> 00:08:21,166
更容易判断你
To judge you more easily

241
00:08:21,233 --> 00:08:22,100
你会发现
You'll find

242
00:08:22,200 --> 00:08:24,933
很多人现在最大的问题不是不努力
That many people's biggest problem today isn't not working hard enough

243
00:08:25,033 --> 00:08:27,566
而是努力没有沉淀成证据
It's that their effort hasn't solidified into evidence

244
00:08:27,700 --> 00:08:28,833
看了很多书
They've read a lot of books

245
00:08:29,033 --> 00:08:30,233
但别人看不到
But others can't see it

246
00:08:30,400 --> 00:08:31,733
用了很多 AI
They've used AI a lot

247
00:08:31,933 --> 00:08:33,100
但没有作品
But they have no work to show

248
00:08:33,233 --> 00:08:34,700
懂了很多道理
They understand many principles

249
00:08:34,800 --> 00:08:36,833
但没有一个稳定输出的地方
But they have no stable output channel

250
00:08:37,100 --> 00:08:39,000
这就像古代一个人很有想法
It's like someone in ancient times with great ideas

251
00:08:39,166 --> 00:08:41,400
但所有想法都只停在嘴里
But all the ideas stayed in their mouth

252
00:08:41,600 --> 00:08:43,300
风一吹，就散了
One gust of wind, and they scattered

253
00:08:43,400 --> 00:08:45,566
普通人要改变这个局面
Ordinary people need to change this

254
00:08:45,766 --> 00:08:47,533
不用一上来追求完美
You don't have to pursue perfection right away

255
00:08:47,633 --> 00:08:49,300
先做三件很小的事
Start with three small things

256
00:08:49,500 --> 00:08:52,400
第一，把你学到的东西写成自己的话
First, write what you've learned in your own words

257
00:08:52,633 --> 00:08:54,233
不要只复制原句
Don't just copy the original sentences

258
00:08:54,400 --> 00:08:56,400
因为复制只能证明你看过
Because copying only proves you've seen it

259
00:08:56,500 --> 00:08:58,833
改写才开始证明你理解过
Rewriting is what proves you've understood it

260
00:08:59,000 --> 00:09:02,100
第二，把你的判断放进真实场景
Second, put your judgment into real scenarios

261
00:09:02,200 --> 00:09:04,633
不要只说“纸降低知识成本”。
Don't just say paper lowered knowledge costs

262
00:09:04,733 --> 00:09:05,900
你要能说出
You should be able to explain

263
00:09:06,100 --> 00:09:09,433
为什么一张试卷会改变家庭气氛
Why one exam paper can change a family's atmosphere

264
00:09:09,566 --> 00:09:12,300
为什么一个账号会变成新的简历
Why one account can become a new resume

265
00:09:12,433 --> 00:09:14,433
为什么 AI 生成内容越多
Why the more content AI generates

266
00:09:14,433 --> 00:09:16,766
普通人越需要自己的判断
The more ordinary people need their own judgment

267
00:09:16,966 --> 00:09:19,300
第三，持续留下作品
Third, consistently produce work

268
00:09:19,433 --> 00:09:21,100
不要等完全准备好
Don't wait until you're fully ready

269
00:09:21,233 --> 00:09:24,100
纸最可惜的用法，不是写错
The saddest use of paper isn't writing something wrong

270
00:09:24,233 --> 00:09:25,633
而是永远空着
It's leaving it blank forever

271
00:09:25,766 --> 00:09:27,900
一个普通人最大的浪费
The biggest waste for an ordinary person

272
00:09:27,900 --> 00:09:29,500
也不是作品不完美
Isn't imperfect work

273
00:09:29,633 --> 00:09:32,233
而是所有思考都没有留下痕迹
It's all that thinking leaving no trace

274
00:09:32,433 --> 00:09:33,433
回到开头
Back to the beginning

275
00:09:33,633 --> 00:09:35,833
一张纸为什么改变了中国人的命运？
Why did one piece of paper change Chinese people's destiny?

276
00:09:35,933 --> 00:09:37,800
不是因为纸很神奇
It wasn't because paper was magical

277
00:09:37,933 --> 00:09:40,100
而是因为它让知识可以复制
It was because it let knowledge be copied

278
00:09:40,233 --> 00:09:41,733
让能力可以留下
Let ability leave a mark

279
00:09:41,900 --> 00:09:43,333
让人可以被比较
Let people be compared

280
00:09:43,533 --> 00:09:45,033
让机会可以被记录
Let opportunity be recorded

281
00:09:45,233 --> 00:09:47,233
纸改变的不是文字
Paper didn't change writing

282
00:09:47,433 --> 00:09:49,800
是社会看见普通人的方式
It changed how society sees ordinary people

283
00:09:49,933 --> 00:09:51,900
而今天，AI 时代也一样
And today, the AI era is the same

284
00:09:52,100 --> 00:09:55,533
真正改变你的，不是你问了多少答案
What truly changes you isn't how many answers you've asked for

285
00:09:55,700 --> 00:09:57,400
而是你留下了什么作品
It's what work you've left behind

286
00:09:57,533 --> 00:09:59,400
你以为命运是被想出来的
You think destiny is imagined

287
00:09:59,600 --> 00:10:00,933
其实很多时候
But often

288
00:10:01,333 --> 00:10:02,800
命运是被写下来
Destiny is written down

289
00:10:02,966 --> 00:10:04,033
被看见
Seen

290
00:10:04,133 --> 00:10:05,033
被比较
Compared

291
00:10:05,300 --> 00:10:06,900
然后被选择的
Then chosen

292
00:10:07,133 --> 00:10:08,500
关注像素呼吸
Follow Pixel Breath

293
00:10:08,666 --> 00:10:09,466
下一条
Next time

294
00:10:09,533 --> 00:10:11,800
我们继续用一件你每天见过的东西
We'll continue using something you see every day

295
00:10:12,033 --> 00:10:14,166
讲透一个你没看懂的社会规则
To break down a social rule you haven't understood yet

296
00:10:14,300 --> 00:10:15,533
我们聊一杯茶
Let's talk about a cup of tea

297
00:10:15,800 --> 00:10:18,000
它最反直觉的地方在于
Here's the most counterintuitive part

298
00:10:18,300 --> 00:10:19,566
茶不是饮料
Tea isn't a drink

299
00:10:19,766 --> 00:10:21,400
而是中国人最温和
It's the most gentle

300
00:10:21,400 --> 00:10:23,433
也最复杂的一种社交货币
And most complex social currency in China

301
00:10:23,600 --> 00:10:24,433
我们下期见
See you next time
